<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-226-248 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 377 301</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Feb 4 1991 n627 p20(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Chip framework agreed to: Japan, U.S. move closer to semi-tradeaccord.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lammers, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The current five-year US-Japanese Semiconductor Trade Agreementexpires in Jul 1991 and US officials are already beginning to workon a new agreement that will hopefully increase market share forforeign-based suppliers.andP;  The Japanese Ministry of InternationalTrade and Industry (MITI) says that it basically supports thisincreased market share.andP;  The Semiconductor Industry Associationand the Computer Systems Policy Project have also proposed anelimination of the fair market value system.andP;  MITI cautiouslysupports this, but officials added that they cannot guarantee anycertain market share.andP;  MITI also opposes the use of sanctions bythe US in the event that market share does not rise as anticipatedby US officials.andP;  In the Jul-to-Sep 1990 quarter, foreign-basedsemiconductor companies held 13.1 percent of the Japanese market,according to the World Semiconductor Trade Statistics council.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Semiconductor IndustryInternational TradeJapanese CompetitionMarket ShareJapan. Ministry of International Trade and IndustrySemiconductor Industry Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>